        {
            "review_id": "226749753",
            "steam_id": "76561197971434473",
            "playtime_minutes": 293,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 1,
            "weighted_score": 0.5025380849838257,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "EA Review: A hell of a lot of fun with mates or randos. The comedic backdrop paired with some of the familiar games such as liars dice or holdem, really do make this original enough to play. I didnt play many ranked matches, however, I found the community in casual games to be a lot of fun.\n\nLoved the setting and characters, all of which made me laugh along the way. Well worth the low price. Looking forward to more updates and a full release."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226886329",
            "steam_id": "76561199209112579",
            "playtime_minutes": 154,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 1,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "👍 Recommended\n🕒 2.6 hours on record  \n\nLiars Bar is a fun and chaotic social deduction game that shines brightest in the first few hours. The core gameplay revolves around bluffing, reading people, and calling out lies, which creates some genuinely funny and tense moments — especially when playing with a group of friends or in voice chat.\n\nWhat stands out is the variety of personalities you meet online. You’ll encounter everything from chill and funny players to absolute chaos agents and toxic ones. This makes every match unpredictable and keeps things entertaining… at least initially.\n\nHowever, after a few hours the game starts to lose its charm. The rounds can feel repetitive, and without a strong group to play with, it becomes less enjoyable. The fun heavily depends on who you’re matched with.\n\nOverall, Liars Bar is a decent party-style game that delivers some good laughs and memorable moments early on. It’s best experienced with friends, and I’d definitely recommend grabbing it on sale rather than at full price.\n\nSolid little bluffing game with personality, but it doesn’t have a lot of long-term staying power. 👍"
        },
