        {
            "review_id": "225774568",
            "steam_id": "76561199518420106",
            "playtime_minutes": 719,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Well, I would certainly and without a doubt say that the game worths its money and it has no problems whatsoever if there were not. I like the minigames and graphics for sure, i'm not questioning any of that. However, the optimization sucks. Geniunely, I've spent probably 3 hours out of 11 being stuck in the endless loading screens or having 3 frames per second for no reason. The game won't run sometimes, again, for no reason. Also, it doesn't let your friends to join the lobby you're in if the game isn't in a mood today, it is what it is. I really enjoy playing the game and really hate dealing with its techincal problems. Stll, would recommend to play if you're not easy to ragebait. The game itself worths it."
        },
