        {
            "review_id": "225608612",
            "steam_id": "76561197999336259",
            "playtime_minutes": 214,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Super fun game, that can be really hilarious, if you're mature enough for some dark humor.\nThere are some bugs (matches that won't progress and are stuck in limbo), but there are no downsides to quitting and queuing again. You might lose some points, but all cosmetics are free anyway.\n\nI don't understand the complaints about the voices. They sound great. Bette than in 90% of indie games.\nMany small games would be improved with voices like this.\n\nIt's easy to find a match for Liar's Deck and Liar's Poker. But my favorite mode (Liar's Dice) has a really hard time finding any players. \n(It's Snow Day from Rocket League all over again ...)\n\nYou have to select a server pool - US/EU/AS.\nIt would be easier to find matches, if all these pools were combined.\nMaybe add a fourth \"ALL\" selection. It's not like ping/latency matters.\n\nGraphics are a bit meh.\nThe style is nice, but aside from the player characters, the asset details and animations are barely a step up from old Telltale games. Some of the UI elements in the menu look very low resolution, like they are from a Switch 1 game. And there is no HDR support, so you have to use RTX HDR. (Which looks great in this game, with its dark, half-lit bar rooms.)\n\nA tutorial/singleplayer mode against CPU would be nice.\nAn official, ambidextrous Steam Controller layout would be nice too. \n\nBut all in all, this is still very fun and amusing, if your not overly sensitive."
        },
